data.title: What To Bring
data.meta_description: Alabama's oldest public 4-year university located within a four-city area on the Tennessee River known as the Shoals
data.text:
Large pieces of furniture or items that you cannot move quickly

Pets

Candles / Oil Lamps / Incense

Oil-Based or Wax Electric Air Fresheners

Extension Cords / Power strips that are not UL approved and do not have their own self-contained circuit breaker

Space Heaters

Halogen Lamps

Routers

Weapons / Explosives

Open Coil or Heated Plate Appliances

Cooking Appliances, including, but not limited to: Electric & Charcoal Grills, Oil Popcorn Poppers, Toasters, Toaster Ovens, Hot Plates, Hot Pots, Coffeemakers, Ovens, Griddles. (As detailed above, microwaves, fridges, and keurigs.)

Adhesives / Attachments that may damage walls or doors, including, but not limited to double-stick tape, duct tape, box tape, electrical tape, command hooks, nails, wallpaper, mirrors, and message boards

U-Hauls and/or Trailers

Restricted items / appliances will be confiscated by HRL and may result in a violation of the student code of conduct.
